title: For Sale:  Glock 19, Fraternal Order of Police 1989 Inaugural, Washington D.C.
postcontent:
I believe this Glock 19 is the first commemorative Glock ever made and it is a true closet queen. These, with the FOP engraving on the side, were available to members of the Metropolitan Police Department, Washington, DC in 1989 when the department converted from revolvers to the Glocks. These were not issued by the government, they were offered thru the FOP lodge from Glock.

Departmental communication in those days was by "Teletype" machines. I have an original teletype, dated May 30, 1989, announcing the arrival of the Glocks ordered prior to March 1, 1989. I cannot imagine that there is another nut out there that has this message from 1989...my bet is that this is the only one that exists and it links this gun historically.

This pistol was made in April 1989 and after I first picked it up on June 1, 1989, I fired 20 rounds thru it. I put it away after that and never fired it. So it is in truly new condition.

Included, with the gun (which has regular white sights, not the glow type) and teletype message, is the original box, manual, two 15 round magazines, a magazine loading assist tool, a Glock #45 holster, original unused bore brush and cleaning rod. I also have the original invoice from Glock for the original purchase dated May 1989.

I am not a FFL holder, so $50 shipping from my local FFL holder to yours, or face to face with no charge to a fellow resident of Virginia

Here is a complete document list:

Original Manual, dated March 1988
Original Invoice from Glock for pistol, dated May 12, 1989
Original Invoice from Glock for holster, dated November 29, 1989
Original White Warranty Card (Owner half, completed – it appears half was returned to Glock)
Original Gun Dealer Transfer Receipt
Original Undated Bulletin from Glock regarding:
Pistol Box Safety Labels
Firearm Safety Booklet
Preventative Maintenance Pamphlet
(all three documents are included and safety labels have not been attached to box)
Original MPDC Teletype message, dated May 30, 1989
MPDC printed Firearm Safety Rules and Inspection Procedures, Form # UN 461, 11/89
MPDC (copy) of oil instructions, Revised 5/90

MPDC uniform shoulder patch.
